SD
Target of 59CO with thickness of 1.00 mg/cm2 was used.
Two detector telescopes were mounted
on rotatable arms on opposite sides of the beam axis,
in the same reaction plane. Each telescope consisted of
a single doublesided SSD as a dE detector, followed by
a single NaI stopping E detector.
The SSD have 16 vertical anode strips and 16 horizontal
cathode strips each, with an active area of
50 mm x 50 mm. The inter-strip gaps are 100 mu-min
width. The stopping detectors used have NaI(Tl)
crystals of 3 inch in diam. and 2 inch thickness.
Statistical uncertainty
